The family of late Samsung Electronics chairman Lee Kun-hee held a funeral ceremony on Wednesday for the patriarch, whose death on Sunday threw into question the control of the chipmaker and South Korea's largest conglomerate.After a morning ceremony closed to the media, family members, including Lee's son Lee Jae-yong, boarded a bus, which left the Samsung Medical Center, where the funeral services had been held, local media Yonhap News TV channel showed.Reuters 
